The paper discusses a control algorithm for a robot to execute contact-rich manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm involves optimization and trade-offs, which suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of vision sensors to detect the environment, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV). The concept of hybrid servoing involves maintaining contacts with the environment, which could be seen as a control systems (cs.SY) problem. Finally, the paper proposes a method to compute force and velocity controls, which could be considered as an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) approach.
